PERTURBATIONS AROUND THE MATTER-SUPPORTED MINIMUM (b < 0)
==============================================================

We start from the action

    S = ∫ d^4x √(-g) [

            R/(16πG)
          - 1/2 (∇M)^2
          - a M^4 / 4
          + b T M^2
          + L_b

        ].

For dust,

    T = -ρ_b

so

    V_eff(M) = a M^4/4 + b ρ_b M^2

For b < 0:

    b = -|b|

    V_eff = a M^4/4 - |b| ρ_b M^2


--------------------------------------------------------------
1. MATTER-SUPPORTED MINIMUM
--------------------------------------------------------------

    dV_eff/dM = a M^3 - 2 |b| ρ_b M = 0

    M = 0
    M_*^2 = 2 |b| ρ_b / a

    M_* = ± sqrt(2 |b| ρ_b / a)

    M_* ∝ a_cos^(-3/2)


--------------------------------------------------------------
2. CURVATURE AT MINIMUM
--------------------------------------------------------------

    d²V_eff/dM² = 3 a M^2 - 2 |b| ρ_b

At minimum:

    m_*^2 = 4 |b| ρ_b > 0


--------------------------------------------------------------
3. FIELD EXPANSION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    M = M_* + χ


--------------------------------------------------------------
4. BACKGROUND EVOLUTION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    M_* ∝ a_cos^(-3/2)

    Ṁ_* = -(3/2) H M_*
    M̈_* = -(3/2) Ḣ M_* + (9/4) H^2 M_*


--------------------------------------------------------------
5. LINEARIZED χ EQUATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    χ̈ + 3H χ̇ + ( k^2/A^2 + m_*^2 ) χ = source

    m_*^2 = 4 |b| ρ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
6. MINIMUM SHIFT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    M_*^2 = 2 |b| ρ_b / a

    δM_* = (M_*/2) (δρ_b / ρ_b)

         = (M_*/2) δ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
7. QUASI-STATIC RESPONSE
--------------------------------------------------------------

    χ ≈ [ m_*^2 / (k^2/A^2 + m_*^2) ] δM_*

    χ ≈ [ m_*^2 / (k^2/A^2 + m_*^2) ] (M_*/2) δ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
8. MEMORY DENSITY PERTURBATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    δρ_M = β_*(k,a) δρ_b

    β_* ∝ [ m_*^2 / (k^2/A^2 + m_*^2) ] × O(M_*^2)


--------------------------------------------------------------
9. EFFECTIVE NEWTON CONSTANT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    (k^2/A^2) Φ = 4πG [1 + β_*] δρ_b

    G_eff = G [1 + β_*]

    β_* < 0 → suppressed growth


--------------------------------------------------------------
10. LIMITS
--------------------------------------------------------------

Small scales:

    k^2/A^2 >> m_*^2

    β_* → 0 → GR recovered

Large scales:

    k^2/A^2 << m_*^2

    β_* → maximum suppression


--------------------------------------------------------------
11. INTERPRETATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    • matter activates field
    • field sits in density-dependent minimum
    • perturbations = shifts of minimum
    • Yukawa screening
    • suppressed growth


--------------------------------------------------------------
12. REDSHIFT DEPENDENCE
--------------------------------------------------------------

    m_*^2 ∝ a_cos^(-3)

→ early: screened
→ late: unscreened


--------------------------------------------------------------
13. MULTISCALE STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------

    cosmology → M ≈ M_*(ρ_b)

    perturbations → screened χ

    galaxies → nonlinear transport

        M^3 ∝ g_b g_obs


--------------------------------------------------------------
14. MAIN RESULT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    M_*^2 = 2 |b| ρ_b / a

    m_*^2 = 4 |b| ρ_b

    G_eff = G [1 + β_*]

    β_* < 0 → suppressed clustering


==============================================================
LEADING-ORDER β_*(k,a)
==============================================================

    m_*^2 = 4 |b| ρ_b

    δM_* = (M_*/2) δ_b

    Y(k,a) = m_*^2 / (k^2/A^2 + m_*^2)

    χ = (M_*/2) Y δ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
β_* DERIVATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    V_eff(M_*) = - |b|^2 ρ_b^2 / a

    δρ_M ≈ - (2 |b|^2 / a) ρ_b δρ_b

Include screening:

    δρ_M ≈ - (2 |b|^2 / a) ρ_b Y δρ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
FINAL β_*
--------------------------------------------------------------

    β_*(k,a)
      ≈ - (8 |b|^3 / a)
          ρ_b^2
          / (k^2/A^2 + 4 |b| ρ_b)


--------------------------------------------------------------
LIMITS
--------------------------------------------------------------

Large scales:

    β_* ≈ - (2 |b|^2 / a) ρ_b

Small scales:

    β_* ∝ - k^(-2)


--------------------------------------------------------------
DIMENSIONLESS FORM
--------------------------------------------------------------

    κ_M^2 = 4 |b| ρ_b A^2

    B(a) = (2 |b|^2 / a) ρ_b

    β_* ≈ - B(a) [ κ_M^2 / (k^2 + κ_M^2) ]


==============================================================
GROWTH EQUATION (N = ln a)
==============================================================

    δ'' + [ 2 + d ln H/dN ] δ'
      = (3/2) Ω_b(a) [1 + β_*(k,a)] δ


--------------------------------------------------------------
LIMITS
--------------------------------------------------------------

k << κ_M:

    β_* ≈ -B(a)

k >> κ_M:

    β_* → 0


--------------------------------------------------------------
GR LIMIT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    b → 0 → β_* → 0


==============================================================
GROWTH RATE AND INDEX
==============================================================

    f = δ'/δ

    f' + f^2 + [ 2 + d ln H/dN ] f
      = (3/2) Ω_b(a) [1 + β_*]


--------------------------------------------------------------
ANSATZ
--------------------------------------------------------------

    f ≈ Ω_m^γ

    β_* < 0 → γ > 0.55


